> there isn&#x27;t a clean way to make &#x27;unit types&#x27; (second, millisecond, meters, etc) in Rust..<p>Actually, there&#x27;s this bit on Tuple Structs[1] in the tutorial:<p>> Types like this can be useful to differentiate between data that have the same underlying type but must be used in different ways.<p><pre><code>  struct Inches(int);
  struct Centimeters(int);
</code></pre>
